sun.jvm.hotspot.utilities

Class RBNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • sun.jvm.hotspot.utilities.RBNode
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IntervalNode

    public class RBNode
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements a node in a red-black tree. It provides accessors for the left and right children as well as the color of the node.

      • getData

      • copyFrom

        public void copyFrom(RBNode arg)
        Must copy all user-defined fields from the given node. For example, the base implementation copies the "data" field. However, it does not (and must not) copy the link fields (parent, left child, right child). It also does not need to copy any computed information for the node, as the node will be updated when necessary. Subclasses must be careful to call the superclass implementation.

      • update

        public boolean update()
        This is called by the base RBTree's insertion and deletion methods when necessary. Subclasses can use this to update any computed information based on the information in their left or right children. For multi-node updates it is guaranteed that this method will be called in the correct order. This should return true if an update actually occurred, false if not.
